# Rule: .github/workflows/release.yml

PR 1 ships an empty placeholder so the file exists and is `.md`-tracked.
The first release PR (Phase 6+) fills it in with the release workflow:
npm publish with OIDC, GitHub release creation, and changelog
synchronisation.

Until then the file body is a comment that says exactly that.
